																		AF2016 Entry, Attributions, and Other Matters
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610183087" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;" >MrWrong</a></span> <span class="odate time_1459561211 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Apr 2016 01:40</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2483877">
									

<p>For the record, if I get to choose the title, it would have been &quot;Fanservice Galore&quot;. And word count is: 1372. Link to fanfic.net counterpart: <a href="https://www.fanfiction.net/s/11874633/1/">https://www.fanfiction.net/s/11874633/1/</a></p>
<p>And the link in the &quot;disclaimer&quot; is my tribute to Love Live, who had recently concluded their last &quot;one-man Live&quot; on 1 April. May their songs be heard.</p>
<p>This is my entry for the 2016 crackfic contest, where I am supposed to write &quot;SCP the Anime, part 4&quot;.</p>
<p>SCPs mentioned are:</p>
<ul>
<li>SCP-140 (An Incomplete Chronicle) by AssertiveRoland</li>
<li>SCP-239 (The Witch Child) by Danteson</li>
<li>SCP-336 (Lilith) by Dr Kondraki</li>
<li>SCP-408 (Illusory Butterflies) by Dr. Kondraki</li>
</ul>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Characters featured are:</p>
<ul>
<li>O5 members</li>
<li>Dr. Judith Low</li>
<li>Dr. Rights</li>
<li>Dr. Light</li>
<li>Dr. Kain</li>
<li>Dr. Bright</li>
<li>Dr. Clef</li>
<li>D.C. al Fine</li>
<li>Dr. Kondraki</li>
<li>Bumaro</li>
<li>Grand Karcist Ion</li>
<li>Marshall Carter (&amp; Dark the rifle)</li>
<li>Nobody's voice</li>
<li>Dr. Gears</li>
<li>Dr. Iceberg</li>
<li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2039383&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1459580526" alt="MrWrong" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2039383)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mrwrong" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2039383); return false;">MrWrong</a></span></li>
</ul>
<p>First scene of part 1 is based on Akira, especially Neo-Site-19. Also cue random generic yandere scene.<br />
Part 2 is an &quot;adaptation&quot; of Clef-Kondraki saga and Fate Stay Night.<sup class="footnoteref"><a id="footnoteref-244282-1" href="javascript:;" class="footnoteref" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.utils.scrollToReference('footnote-244282-1')">1</a></sup><br />
Part 3 is an adaptation of the Japanese folktale <em>Momotaro</em>.<br />
Part 4 is just a clip show.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>And yes, I am really busy and should not be writing articles&#8230; but damn, crackfics in this site is once in a lifetime and those kind of stuff are likely to be among the first things we read about the Foundation.</p>
<div class="footnotes-footer">
<div class="title">Footnotes</div>
